{{for|the administrative subdivision|Gomishan District}} {{redirect|Gomesh Tappeh|the village in Zanjan Province|Gomesh Tappeh, Zanjan}} {{Infobox settlement |official_name =Gomish Tepe |native_name =-گميشان |settlement_type = City |pushpin_map =Iran |mapsize =150px |subdivision_type = [[List of countries|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}} |subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]] |subdivision_name1 =[[Golestan Province|Golestan]] |subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]] |subdivision_name2 =[[Torkaman County|Torkaman]] |subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]] |subdivision_name3 =[[Gomishan District|Gomishan]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = 2016 Census |population_total =19,191 <ref>https://www.amar.org.ir/english</ref> |population_density_km2 =auto |timezone = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]] |utc_offset = +3:30 |timezone_DST = [[Iran Daylight Time|IDST]] |utc_offset_DST = +4:30 |coordinates = {{coord|37|04|18|N|54|04|36|E|region:IR|display=inline,title}} |elevation_m = |area_code = |website = |footnotes ={{GEOnet2|76DAF57E33C7A898E040D6A413F72A9A}} }} '''Gomishan''' ({{lang-fa|گميشان}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Gomīshān''' and '''Gumshān'''; formerly, '''Gomish Tepe''' ({{lang-fa|گميش تپه}}), also Romanized as '''Gomesh Tappeh''', '''Gomīsh Tappeh''', and '''Gumish Tepe'''; also formerly known as '''Gomish Tepe Jik''' ({{lang-fa|گُميش تَپِّه جيك}}), also Romanized as '''Gomīsh Tappeh Jīk'''; {{lang-tk|Kümüş depe}})<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3767874}}</ref> is a city and capital of [[Gomishan District]], in [[Torkaman County]], [[Golestan Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census its population was 15,639, in 3,236 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|27}}</ref>
The city's Turkmen name, Kümüş depe, means "Silver Hill".
